NSW – Sydney, QLD – Brisbane, VIC – Melbourne, SA - Adelaide and ACT - Canberra
ERP Migration | TechnologyOne | Aurion 

Our client, a key regulator promoting competition and fair trading, is seeking an experienced Business Analyst to drive the implementation of new systems, processes, and ways of working, helping staff thrive as a standalone Commonwealth agency.

Duties of the Business Analyst

Provide considerable support to team with testing of the new ERP system (Aurion to TechnologyOne), ensuring smooth transition and minimal gaps;
Continue and deliver, document services and workflows as a single source of truth for staff;
Design and refine business processes to support new systems and future-state functions;
Coordinate migration of policy and procedure documents;
Support change management activities, including impact assessments, stakeholder engagement & training documentation;
Drive continuous improvement in business analysis practices and ways of working.

Skills and Experience Required

Experience with TechnologyOne or comparable ERP systems;
Strong capability in business analysis techniques, process design, and documentation;
Ability to quickly understand new domains and translate complex problems into practical solutions;
Excellent stakeholder engagement skills, with the ability to influence, negotiate, and resolve sensitive issue;
Clear and concise communication skills, both written and verbal (especially to staff at a senior level);
Ability to support Change Management experience within large organisations.

